- If the user explicitly requests a countdown, or the edit clearly introduces a limited-time offer, deadline, launch window, expiring deal, or sale end, treat it as a countdown use case.
- Require a specific date, time, and timezone. If any of that is missing, ask: "What date and time should the countdown target? Please provide the specific date, time, and your timezone (e.g., 'December 25, 2025 at 6:00 PM EST' or 'January 15, 2026 at 2:30 PM Pacific Time'). I need your timezone to convert it to UTC properly."
- Set clientFeatures.countdown.targetDate to the UTC ISO target date.
- Output countdown HTML as a sticky banner at the top of the page.
- Preserve the runtime DOM contract exactly: root id="countdown-timer"; a countdown display with child markers data-time-unit="days", "hours", "minutes", and "seconds"; each unit must contain a span the injected runtime can update; and keep the CTA button in the banner.
- Keep the banner initially hidden with styles compatible with runtime reveal behavior, such as opacity: 0 and visibility: hidden, so zero values do not flash before injection runs.
- Do not add custom countdown JavaScript unless the user explicitly asks for it. The runtime injects countdown behavior, updates the numbers, and removes the banner when the countdown ends.
- When editing an existing countdown, do not rename or remove the required id and data-time-unit markers.`;(0,tC.tool)({description:s0(),inputSchema:sQ,execute:async(e,t)=>{let r=e.title.length>40?`${e.title.slice(0,39)}\u2026`:e.title;l(t,{message:`Editing "${r}" \u2728\u{1F525}`});let n={html:e.html||"",title:e.title||"",description:e.description||""};return e.htmlDescription&&(n.htmlDescription=e.htmlDescription),e.clientFeatures&&(n.clientFeatures=e.clientFeatures),n}});var s1=d.object({preciseEditExpected:d.boolean().default(!0).describe("Indicates whether the user expects precise edits to the element"),xpath:d.string().describe("XPath location of the element in the DOM"),elementHtml:d.string().optional().describe("Clean HTML of the element without inline styles. Return original HTML if preciseEditExpected is true. Omit if element should be removed. MUST be a single-line minified string with no literal newlines."),shouldRemove:d.boolean().optional().describe("Set to true if the element should be completely removed"),prompt:d.string().describe("User's instruction for what changes to make to the element")}),s4=()=>`
Edit a specific element on a landing page. Set preciseEditExpected=true for element-level changes (text, color, size, styling) or false for page-level changes (new sections, layout redesign). When in doubt, default to true. Use inline styles for all style changes. Set shouldRemove=true to delete the element.

If the element is part of a countdown or limited-time banner, preserve the runtime hooks exactly: do not rename or remove id="countdown-timer", data-time-unit markers, or the span value elements inside those unit containers unless the user explicitly asks to remove the countdown entirely. Do not add custom countdown JavaScript unless explicitly requested.`;(0,tC.tool)({description:s4(),inputSchema:s1,execute:async(e,t)=>{let r=e.prompt.length>45?`${e.prompt.slice(0,44)}\u2026`:e.prompt;return l(t,{message:`"${r}" \u2728`}),e}});var s6=d.object({statusMessages:d.array(d.string()).describe("Array of exactly 10 friendly status messages tailored to the user's landing page edit request. Messages should be helpful, a bit playful, and avoid overly technical language. Each message MUST be a single-line string with no literal newlines.")});(0,tC.tool)({description:'Generate exactly 10 friendly, playful status messages tailored to the edit request. Messages should sound like a helpful friend working on the page. The 10th message should NOT indicate completion — keep it in progress (e.g., "Almost there!").',inputSchema:s6,execute:async e=>({statusMessages:e.statusMessages})});var s3={};o(s3,{$brand:()=>s8,$input:()=>h7,$output:()=>h5,NEVER:()=>s5,TimePrecision:()=>mD,ZodAny:()=>b_,ZodArray:()=>bC,ZodBase64:()=>vH,ZodBase64URL:()=>vY,ZodBigInt:()=>bl,ZodBigIntFormat:()=>bc,ZodBoolean:()=>bo,ZodCIDRv4:()=>vJ,ZodCIDRv6:()=>vV,ZodCUID:()=>vT,ZodCUID2:()=>vO,ZodCatch:()=>yd,ZodCodec:()=>yg,ZodCustom:()=>yA,ZodCustomStringFormat:()=>v3,ZodDate:()=>bA,ZodDefault:()=>yr,ZodDiscriminatedUnion:()=>bP,ZodE164:()=>v0,ZodEmail:()=>vg,ZodEmoji:()=>vA,ZodEnum:()=>bY,ZodError:()=>g7,ZodFile:()=>b6,ZodFirstPartyTypeKind:()=>t,ZodFunction:()=>yS,ZodGUID:()=>vb,ZodIPv4:()=>vZ,ZodIPv6:()=>vq,ZodISODate:()=>g0,ZodISODateTime:()=>gY,ZodISODuration:()=>g3,ZodISOTime:()=>g4,ZodIntersection:()=>bF,ZodIssueCode:()=>yN,ZodJWT:()=>v4,ZodKSUID:()=>vR,ZodLazy:()=>yw,ZodLiteral:()=>b1,ZodMap:()=>bV,ZodNaN:(